article.description: Jefferson's 29, Wright's career-high 21 lead Nets' opening-night 112-103 win over Chicago.
article.headline: Bulls rally but fall to Nets in OT as Kobe rumors rage on
article.linkText: Wright outduels Gordon as Nets beat Bulls in OT
article.story: EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Unwanted Antoine Wright scored 14 of his career-high 21 points in the fourth quarter and overtime to lead the New Jersey Nets to a 112-103 victory over the distracted Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night. Richard Jefferson added 29 points and 10 rebounds, Vince Carter had 24 points and a big steal late and Jason Kidd handed out 13 assists to lead the Nets to their 12th straight win over Chicago in New Jersey. Ben Gordon had 27 points and Luol Deng added 22 points and 11 rebounds for the Bulls, who have been distracted in recent days by rumors of a possible major trade for Kobe Bryant. It took Chicago more than a half to get going and a major effort by Gordon to rally them from a 15-point deficit. It wasn't enough to overcome Wright, who was told by the Nets last week that they would not be picking up the option on his contract for next season. On the opening night of the season, he enhanced his future free agency status.
